    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Device having one or more bells mounted to a wheel, the turning of which rings the bells, usually clapper bells. The devices may be of various sizes and used for various purposes. One use of the device is as a sanctus bell during the Catholic mass.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
